input.prompt:
You are implementing **Phase 2** of a plan to add a Prompt Templates tab to the new-ui dashboard.

## Phase 2: List Page (`/templates`)

Create the templates list page and wire it into the router and sidebar.

### File to Create

**`new-ui/src/pages/templates/page.tsx`** — default export, lazy-loaded page:
- AG Grid with columns: eventType, scope, scopeId, state (badge), version, isDefault (badge), updatedAt (formatted)
- Search input filtering by eventType substring (client-side quick filter on AG Grid via `quickFilterText`)
- Scope dropdown filter: All / global / agent / repo
- isDefault toggle filter
- Row click → navigate to `/templates/:id`
- Empty state when no templates
- Page icon: `FileText` from lucide-react

### Files to Modify

**`new-ui/src/app/router.tsx`**:
- Add lazy import for `TemplatesPage` only (detail pages added in Phase 3)
- Add route: `{ path: "templates", element: &lt;TemplatesPage /&gt; }`

**`new-ui/src/components/layout/app-sidebar.tsx`**:
- Add `FileText` to lucide imports
- Add `{ title: "Templates", path: "/templates", icon: FileText }` to the "Communication" nav group

### PATTERNS TO FOLLOW

**Page structure** (from agents/page.tsx, tasks/page.tsx):
```tsx
export default function TemplatesPage() {
  // hooks, state, columnDefs, etc.
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col flex-1 min-h-0 gap-4">
      <h1 className="text-xl font-semibold">Templates</h1>
      <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
        {/* Search input + filter dropdowns */}
      </div>
      <DataGrid ... />
    </div>
  );
}
```

**DataGrid usage**:
```tsx
import { DataGrid } from "@/components/ui/data-grid";

<DataGrid
  rowData={filteredData}
  columnDefs={columnDefs}
  quickFilterText={search}
  onRowClicked={handleRowClick}
  loading={isLoading}
  emptyMessage="No templates found"
  getRowId={(params) => String(params.data?.id)}
/>
```

**AG Grid column definitions**:
```tsx
const columnDefs = useMemo<ColDef<PromptTemplate>[]>(() => [
  { field: "eventType", headerName: "Event Type", flex: 1, minWidth: 200 },
  { field: "scope", headerName: "Scope", width: 100 },
  // ... badges use cellRenderer with Badge component
  {
    field: "isDefault",
    headerName: "Default",
    width: 100,
    cellRenderer: (params: { value: boolean }) =>
      params.value ? <Badge variant="secondary">Default</Badge> : null,
  },
  {
    field: "updatedAt",
    headerName: "Updated",
    width: 150,
    valueFormatter: (params) => params.value ? formatSmartTime(params.value) : "",
  },
], []);
```

**Row click handler**:
```tsx
const navigate = useNavigate();
const handleRowClick = useCallback(
  (event: RowClickedEvent<PromptTemplate>) => {
    if (event.data?.id) navigate(`/templates/${event.data.id}`);
  },
  [navigate],
);
```

**Filter with Select dropdown** (shadcn):
```tsx
import { Select, SelectContent, SelectItem, SelectTrigger, SelectValue } from "@/components/ui/select";

<Select value={scopeFilter} onValueChange={setScopeFilter}>
  <SelectTrigger className="w-[140px]">
    <SelectValue placeholder="All scopes" />
  </SelectTrigger>
  <SelectContent>
    <SelectItem value="all">All scopes</SelectItem>
    <SelectItem value="global">Global</SelectItem>
    <SelectItem value="agent">Agent</SelectItem>
    <SelectItem value="repo">Repo</SelectItem>
  </SelectContent>
</Select>
```

**Search input**:
```tsx
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Search } from "lucide-react";

<div className="relative">
  <Search className="absolute left-2.5 top-2.5 size-4 text-muted-foreground" />
  <Input
    placeholder="Search event types..."
    value={search}
    onChange={(e) => setSearch(e.target.value)}
    className="pl-8 w-[250px]"
  />
</div>
```

**isDefault toggle** (use a Button or Switch):
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<Button
  variant={showDefaultsOnly ? "default" : "outline"}
  size="sm"
  onClick={() => setShowDefaultsOnly(!showDefaultsOnly)}
>
  Defaults only
</Button>
```

**Sidebar nav group** — The Communication group in app-sidebar.tsx looks like:
```tsx
{
  label: "Communication",
  items: [
    { title: "Chat", path: "/chat", icon: MessageSquare },
    // Add here:
    { title: "Templates", path: "/templates", icon: FileText },
  ],
},
```

**Router** — lazy import pattern:
```tsx
const TemplatesPage = lazy(() => import("@/pages/templates/page"));
// In routes array:
{ path: "templates", element: <TemplatesPage /> },
```

### Data Filtering

The `usePromptTemplates` hook accepts filters: `{ eventType?: string; scope?: string; isDefault?: boolean }`.
For the list page, use server-side filtering via the hook params for scope and isDefault, and client-side AG Grid `quickFilterText` for eventType search.

Actually, simpler approach: fetch all templates with `usePromptTemplates()` (no filters), then:
- Use `quickFilterText={search}` on DataGrid for eventType search
- Filter `rowData` in JS for scope and isDefault filters before passing to DataGrid

### Imports you'll need

```tsx
import { usePromptTemplates } from "@/api/hooks";
import type { PromptTemplate } from "@/api/types";
import { DataGrid } from "@/components/ui/data-grid";
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Select, SelectContent, SelectItem, SelectTrigger, SelectValue } from "@/components/ui/select";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Search, FileText } from "lucide-react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";
import { useCallback, useMemo, useState } from "react";
import type { ColDef, RowClickedEvent } from "ag-grid-community";
import { formatSmartTime } from "@/lib/utils"; // Check if this exists, otherwise use a simple date formatter
```

### Verification

After implementing, run:
```bash
cd new-ui && pnpm exec tsc --noEmit && pnpm build
```

Fix any errors before reporting completion.

### Important
- Read existing files FULLY before modifying (router.tsx, app-sidebar.tsx)
- Match existing code style exactly (2-space indent, double quotes)
- Check what imports already exist before adding duplicates
- Verify `formatSmartTime` exists in the utils — if not, use a simple `new Date(val).toLocaleDateString()` or find the actual date formatting util used in the project
- Do NOT create detail page files or routes — that's Phase 3

