You are implementing **Phase 4** (final phase) of a plan to add Prompt Templates to the new-ui dashboard.

## Phase 4: Polish + Edge Cases

Add loading skeletons, error states, toast notifications, and keyboard shortcuts to the template pages.

### Files to Modify

#### 1. `new-ui/src/pages/templates/page.tsx` (list page)
- Add loading skeleton when `isLoading` is true — look at other pages in `new-ui/src/pages/` for existing loading patterns (some use a simple spinner or skeleton)
- Add error state when query fails (check `isError` / `error` from the hook)

#### 2. `new-ui/src/pages/templates/[id]/page.tsx` (detail page)
- Add loading skeleton for detail page (when `isLoading` from `usePromptTemplate`)
- Add error state for 404 (when `isError` or `!data?.template` after loading)
- Add toast notifications via `sonner` on save/checkout/reset/delete success and failure:
  ```tsx
  import { toast } from "sonner";
  // In mutation onSuccess/onError callbacks:
  toast.success("Template saved");
  toast.error("Failed to save template");
  ```
  Check that `sonner` is available — look for existing usage in the project. If `sonner` is installed and a `<Toaster />` is already mounted in the app layout, just import `toast` from `sonner`. If not, check for alternatives.
- Keyboard shortcut: `Cmd+S` / `Ctrl+S` to save when on the Raw tab (non-default only):
  ```tsx
  useEffect(() => {
    const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
      if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === "s") {
        e.preventDefault();
        if (!template.isDefault) {
          handleSave();
        }
      }
    };
    window.addEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown);
  }, [template?.isDefault, handleSave]);
  ```
  Make sure `handleSave` is wrapped in `useCallback` to avoid stale closures.

#### 3. `new-ui/src/pages/templates/[id]/history/[version]/page.tsx` (version detail page)
- Add loading skeleton
- Add error state for invalid version (version not found in history array)

### Loading Skeleton Pattern

Check existing pages for their loading pattern. A simple approach:
```tsx
if (isLoading) {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col flex-1 min-h-0 gap-4">
      <div className="h-7 w-48 bg-muted animate-pulse rounded" />
      <div className="flex-1 bg-muted/50 animate-pulse rounded" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

Or if the project uses a `Skeleton` component from shadcn:
```tsx
import { Skeleton } from "@/components/ui/skeleton";

if (isLoading) {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col flex-1 min-h-0 gap-4">
      <Skeleton className="h-7 w-48" />
      <Skeleton className="flex-1" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Error State Pattern

```tsx
if (isError || (!isLoading && !template)) {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col flex-1 items-center justify-center gap-2 text-muted-foreground">
      <p>Template not found</p>
      <Button variant="outline" size="sm" asChild>
        <Link to="/templates">Back to Templates</Link>
      </Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Toast Integration

First check if `sonner` is already used in the project:
- Look for `import { toast } from "sonner"` or `<Toaster />` in existing files
- If found, just import and use `toast.success()` / `toast.error()`
- If not found, check if there's another toast system (like `@/components/ui/use-toast`)

Add toasts to these mutations in the detail page:
- Save: `toast.success("Template saved")` / `toast.error("Failed to save template")`
- Checkout: `toast.success("Checked out version ${version}")` / `toast.error("Failed to checkout version")`
- Reset: `toast.success("Template reset to default")` / `toast.error("Failed to reset template")`
- Delete: `toast.success("Template deleted")` / `toast.error("Failed to delete template")`
- Customize: `toast.success("Template customized — you can now edit it")` / `toast.error("Failed to customize template")`

### Verification

```bash
cd new-ui && pnpm lint && pnpm exec tsc --noEmit && pnpm build
```

Fix ALL lint and type errors. Run `pnpm biome check --write .` if needed for formatting.

### Important
- Read all 3 page files FULLY before modifying
- Check existing toast/notification patterns in the project first
- Match code style exactly
- The debounced preview from Phase 3 should already be working — don't break it
- Make sure `handleSave` is a stable `useCallback` reference for the keyboard shortcut

